<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1530,2036]" box="[151,999,1530,1556]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1530,1556]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length (from apex of vertex to tip of fore wings): ď 9.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1530,2036]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">
General color yellowish brown; vertex with one black spot at apex and a blackish linear stripe along the margins of sublateral carinae, carinae on vertex, pronotum and mesonotum reddish; frons with 
<number box="[1242,1257,1610,1636]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" value="5.0">5</number>
carmine transverse bands. Fore wings without nebula apically. Postfemora with reddish stripes. Vertex with sublateral carinae distinctly curved outwards, nearly reaching to lateral margins; lateral areas between sublateral carinae and lateral carinae shallowly depressed. (After 
<bibRefCitation author="Melichar" box="[703,885,1730,1756]" pageId="12" pageNumber="44" refString="Melichar, L. (1914) Monographie der Tropiduchinen (Homoptera). Verhandlungen des Naturforschenden Vereins in Brunn, 53, 1 - 145." type="journal article" year="1914">
Melichar, 
<number box="[822,885,1730,1756]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" value="1914.0">1914</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1530,2036]" box="[197,408,1770,1796]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
